article.headline: High Point 75, Radford 65
article.story: RADFORD, Va. (AP) -- Arizona Reid scored 29 points to lead High Point to a 75-65 win over Radford on Wednesday night, giving the Panthers' their fourth-straight Big South Conference road win. The Panthers (16-6, 7-1) led 30-25 at the half, overcoming a 6-0 run by Radford in the opening minutes. The Highlanders (7-16, 2-6) trailed 55-54 with 8:23 to play on a 3-pointer by Kenny Thomas, but were unable to stop High Point's 20-11 run to finish the game. Reid was the only High Point player to score double-digits. Amir Johnson led Radford with 14 points, Reggie McIntyre added 13 and Martell McDuffy had 12.
